{"name": "Athlete", "type": "class", "img": "icons/magic/control/buff-strength-muscle-damage-orange.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have embarked on a dedicated journey to hone not just your skills to perfection, but your body as well. By cultivating your own physical prowess, you know that you can count on your body to perform when the situation tests your physical limits.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "identifier": "athlete", "restDice": "d12", "manaAtFirstLevel": 0, "manaPerLevel": 0, "categorization": {"martial": {"progression": "full"}, "spellcaster": {"progression": "none"}}, "classDetails": "<h3>Standalone Archetype: Athlete</h3><p><em>Unlock:</em> When you reach 2nd level overall and have at least one level in a Martial class.</p><hr /><h3>Class Features at Higher Levels</h3><p><strong>Class Categorization:</strong>&nbsp;Martial<br /><strong>Rest Dice Gain After 1st Level:</strong> 1d12 per&nbsp;Athlete level<br /><strong>Hit Point Gain After 1st Level:</strong><br /> - 1d12 + your Constitution modifier<br /> - Or&nbsp;7 + your Constitution modifier<br /><strong>Mana:</strong>&nbsp;None</p><hr /><p>&#x1F193; Given Abilities: @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.VXLO74M9FQ5TRHU8]{Athletic}</p><hr /><h3>Athlete Abilities</h3><p>When taking a level in Athlete, you may choose from the following abilities:</p><hr /><p>Options: @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.GOP7M90B2MXBCL8K]{Sprinter}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.17YBBWEXS5QW6W94]{Stalwart Physique}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.KHXTYYWW0CRFP2RN]{Going All-Out}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.MCOVKJ7UZMJQGXIQ]{Tireless}</p>"}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "SGBQSDSKVB1PB8HK", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Deathwarden", "type": "class", "img": "icons/magic/death/weapon-scythe-rune-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>The Deathwardens are a mysterious order of acolytes who guard the separation of life and death. Their qualms are not with necromantic magic in general&mdash;as they incorporate the mastery of such energies into their techniques&mdash;but rather those who would violate the sanctity of graveyards or seek immortality through undeath.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "identifier": "deathwarden", "restDice": "d10", "manaAtFirstLevel": 1, "manaPerLevel": 1, "categorization": {"martial": {"progression": "full"}, "spellcaster": {"progression": "full"}}, "classDetails": "<h3>Standalone Archetype: Deathwarden</h3><p><em>Unlock:</em> When you reach 3rd level overall and have at least one level each in a Martial and Spellcaster class.</p><hr /><h3>Class Features at Higher Levels</h3><p><strong>Class Categorization:</strong>&nbsp;Martial<br /><strong>Rest Dice Gain After 1st Level:</strong> 1d10 per&nbsp;Deathwarden level<br /><strong>Hit Point Gain After 1st Level:</strong><br /> - 1d10 + your Constitution modifier<br /> - Or&nbsp;6 + your Constitution modifier<br /><strong>Mana:</strong>&nbsp;+1</p><p><strong>Spellcasting Attribute:</strong> Abilities in this class use the same spellcasting attribute as your <em>Dread Blade</em> cantrip.</p><p>&#x27A2; Spell Save DC: 8 + your proficiency bonus + your spellcasting attribute modifier.</p><hr /><p>&#x1F193; Given Abilities: @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.5GKWWIQFXU0YBEWB]{Tools of the Harvest}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.WXAA4GO3QQKD1H7M]{Loyal Weapon}</p><hr /><h3>Deathwarden Abilities</h3><p>When taking a level in Deathwarden, you may choose from the following abilities:</p><hr /><p>Options: @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.VP1MJ4K008E0P5QE]{Reaper}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.H5SWPCUEGNVFEPPT]{Thanatophobia}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.GJSBBBEWC3QHE19Y]{One Foot in the Grave}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.5Y5UKK5OB00AYMHG]{Hungering Shadows}</p>"}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "5TLH6H5CXB9YMEK5", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Emberseeker", "type": "class", "img": "icons/magic/fire/projectile-wave-arrow.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>The Emberseekers are an aloof conclave of rangers and woodsfolk. They watch over and guard the ancient cycle of wildfire, ash, sapling, and forest, and bind themselves to elemental spirits of flame in pursuit of this balance. While their methods may seem extreme, they can be relied upon to oppose any monster that threatens the natural cycles of their lands.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "identifier": "emberseeker", "restDice": "d8", "manaAtFirstLevel": 1, "manaPerLevel": 1, "categorization": {"martial": {"progression": "full"}, "spellcaster": {"progression": "full"}}, "classDetails": "<h3>Standalone Archetype: Emberseeker</h3><p><em>Unlock:</em> When you reach 3rd level overall and have at least one level each in a Martial and Spellcaster class.</p><hr /><h3>Class Features at Higher Levels</h3><p><strong>Class Categorization:</strong>&nbsp;Martial<br /><strong>Rest Dice Gain After 1st Level:</strong> 1d8 per&nbsp;Emberseeker level<br /><strong>Hit Point Gain After 1st Level:</strong><br /> - 1d8 + your Constitution modifier<br /> - Or&nbsp;5 + your Constitution modifier<br /><strong>Mana:</strong>&nbsp;+2</p><p><strong>Spellcasting Attribute:</strong> Abilities in this class use the same spellcasting attribute as your @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-cantrips.58I1UTE8ZV4CJ5W6]{Adherent Ember} cantrip.</p><p>&#x27A2; Spell Save DC: 8 + your proficiency bonus + your spellcasting attribute modifier.</p><hr /><p>&#x1F193; Given Abilities: @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.1P73PV63XRZZ06AX]{Seeker's Knack}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.06UDKKP6BQGSGKF8]{Primordial Bond}</p><hr /><h3>Emberseeker Abilities</h3><p>When taking a level in Emberseeker, you may choose from the following abilities:</p><hr /><p>Options: @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.0XE5EBEOURNKXDWE]{Smoldering Quiver}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.RZWY2QVJ74LA8RZ6]{Kindled Companion}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.6Q8NPXGTPOTSP2KO]{Ashen Drift}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.17T1JOINDUGBWTGS]{Fuel the Flames}</p>"}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "2DVAWFZDYJPTVZWY", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
